function minimumPathCost(stones) {
    let n = stones.length;
    let max_cost = stones[n-1];
    for(let i = 1; i < n-1; ++i){
        max_cost = Math.min(max_cost, Math.max(stones[i], stones[n-1]-stones[i]));
    }
    return max_cost;
}
```

    The algorithm calculates the minimum cost of a path for the frog. It first initializes the maximum cost as the last stone. It then iterates through the stones (excluding the first and last one), and at each stone, it calculates the cost of jumping to the last stone and back. It updates the max_cost with the minimum of itself and the current cost. Finally, it returns the max_cost as the result. Since we iterate through the stones once, the time complexity is O(n).

